    "I woke up at 3 AM to the sound of my smoke detector. Not a false alarm. The dryer in our laundry room had caught fire. We got out with the kids, the dog, and nothing else. Standing in the front yard in my underwear, watching firefighters work, I had one thought: 'Please let the insurance cover this.' It did. Eventually. After 14 weeks of calls, paperwork, adjuster visits, contractor negotiations, and temporary housing disputes. The fire took 20 minutes to destroy half my home. The insurance company took 14 weeks to start fixing it.",
